<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="16Feb1931"><font color="red">16 February 1931</font> <i>Letters I and BLHW</i> (to Harriet Weaver, typed): I have sent away four fifths of my books keeping only dictionaries and books of references &hellip; I have been working a great deal at [the French A.L.P.] with Leon and Soupault &hellip; I have also been working with Gorman for his biography &hellip; I am also trying to conclude section 1 of Part II but such an amount of reading seems to be necessary before my old flying machine grumbles up into the air. Personally the only thing that encourages me is my belief that what I have written up to the present is a good deal better than any other first draft I made. My insomnia is better </div>
